The provincial breakdown was as follows: Eastern Cape – 48,232 (18.3 percent) Free State – 4679 (1.8) Gauteng – 93,044 (35.2) KwaZulu-Natal – 23,753 (9.0) Limpopo – 2835 (1.1) Mpumalanga – 3621 (1.4) North West – 9418 (3.6) Northern Cape  – 1266 (0.5) Western Cape – 77,336 (29.3 percent) Unknown – 0 (0.0) A total of 2,108,570 tests had been processed to date, of which 51,338 had been conducted since the previous report on Saturday. “Regrettably, we report a further 111 Covid-19-related deaths – four from the Northern Cape, 13 from KwaZulu-Natal, 26 from Gauteng, 30 from the Eastern Cape, and 38 from the Western Cape. This brings the total number of Covid-19-related deaths to 3971. We convey our condolences to the loved ones of the departed and thank the healthcare workers who treated the deceased. The number of recoveries is 127,715, which translates to a recovery rate of 48.4 percent,” Mkhize said. The provincial breakdown was as follows: Eastern Cape – 664 deaths and 30,917 recoveries Free State – 19 and 681 Gauteng – 580 and 29,038 KwaZulu-Natal – 273 and 6021 Limpopo – 33 and 991 Mpumalanga – 22 and 910 North West – 36 and 1715 Northern Cape – 11 and 308 Western Cape – 2333 deaths and 57,134 recoveries – African News Agency (ANA)